cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the impact of content distribution networks on internet traffic demand. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as transparent caches are mentioned, which can have security implications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a mathematical model for content requests and cache performance. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be relevant as the paper analyzes traffic traces collected on a network. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of a cache based on the proposed model.
